def create_df_from_file():
    
    filenames = []
    documents = []
    threeWD_items = []   

    for file in sorted(os.listdir(directory)):

        #02_Mind, Body & Soul_ The Three Forces of Psychology  Anthony J. Rotolo
        if file.find(FILE_PATTERN) > -1:

            #print(os.path.join(directory, file))

            htmlFile = open(os.path.join(directory, file), 'rb')

            html_page = htmlFile.read()

            soup = BeautifulSoup(html_page, "html.parser")
    
            file_threeWD_items = []
            for tag in ['ol', 'ul']:
                for ol in soup.find_all(tag):

                    lis = ol.find_all('li')

                    if len(lis) == 3:
                        
                        temp = []
                        for child in lis:
                            #print(child.get_text())
                            temp.append(child.get_text())

                        file_threeWD_items.append(temp)
            
            def tag_visible(element):
                if element.parent.name in ['style', 'script', 'head', 'title', 'meta', '[document]']:
                    return False
                if isinstance(element, Comment):
                    return False
                return True


            def text_from_html(body):
                soup = BeautifulSoup(body, 'html.parser')
                texts = soup.findAll(text=True)
                visible_texts = filter(tag_visible, texts)  
                return u" ".join(t.strip() for t in visible_texts)
            
            texts = soup.findAll(text=True)
            visible_texts = filter(tag_visible, texts)
                
            text = u" ".join(t.strip() for t in visible_texts)
         
            text = soup.get_text()
            
            text = re.sub(r'([a-z])\.([A-Z])', r'\1. \2', text)

            documents.append(text)
            filenames.append(file[0:2])
            threeWD_items.append(file_threeWD_items)

    data = pd.DataFrame(data={'documents':documents, 'filenames': filenames, 'LI_3WD_Items':threeWD_items  })
    data['sentences'] = data.documents.progress_map(sent_tokenize)

    data['short_file_name'] = data['filenames'].apply(lambda filename: filename[0:2])
    return data

data = create_df_from_file()

def check_three(item):
    lower_tk = item.lower()
    #print(lower_tk)
    return lower_tk.find("three ") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("triangle") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("triadic") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("trilevel") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("triad") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("trigrams") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("tripod") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("triple") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find("3Cs") > -1 \
        or lower_tk.find(" 3 ") > 0 \
        or lower_tk.find("3 ") == 0

def remove_stop_words(text):
    
    tokens = word_tokenize(text.lower())
    tokens_wo_stopwords = [t for t in tokens if t.strip() not in english_stopwords]
    return " ".join(tokens_wo_stopwords)

def remove_words_before_three(text):
    text = text.lower();
    index = text.find("three")
    if index > -1:
        return text[index:]
    return text
        
def remove_URL(sample):
    """Remove URLs from a sample string"""
    return re.sub(r"http\S+", "", sample)

import re

def replace_AND_by_Comma(phrase):
    if phrase.count(",") == 1 and phrase.find("and")>-1:
        return phrase.replace("and", ",")
    return phrase

def extract_3WD_items(sentence):
    if sentence.find(chr(8212)) > -1:
        sentence = sentence.replace(chr(8212),":")
    elif sentence.find("-") > -1 or sentence.find("") > -1:
        sentence = sentence.replace("",":")
        sentence = sentence.replace("",":")
    elif sentence.find("composed of") > -1:
        sentence = sentence.replace("composed of",":")
    elif sentence.find("namely") > -1:
        sentence = sentence.replace("namely",":")
    elif sentence.find("are to") > -1:
        sentence = sentence.replace("are to",":") # special case
    
    #sentence = sentence.replace(")","") #
    
    parts = sentence.split(":")
    if (len(parts) == 3):
        parts = [parts[0],parts[1]]
        
    result = []
    if (len(parts) == 2):
        words = replace_AND_by_Comma(parts[1]).split(",")
        if len(words) == 3:
            for word in words:
                word = word.replace(" and", "")
                word = word.replace(".", "")
                word = word.strip()
                result.append(word)

    return result;

def handle_special_case(noun_phrase):
    
    parts = noun_phrase.split("")
    if len(parts)> 1:
        return parts[0]
    
    return noun_phrase
In [753]:
def extract_noun_phrases_from_tree(tree, label='NounPhrase', match_three=True):
    noun_phrases = []
    
    def traverse_tree(tree):

        if tree.label() == label:
            noun_phrase = ' '.join([token for token, tag in tree.leaves()])
            
            if match_three:
                
                if check_three(noun_phrase):
                    noun_phrases.append(handle_special_case(noun_phrase))
            else:
                noun_phrases.append(handle_special_case(noun_phrase))


        for subtree in tree:
            if type(subtree) == nltk.tree.Tree:
                traverse_tree(subtree)
    
    traverse_tree(tree)
    
    return noun_phrases
In [754]:
def extract_3WD_ITEMS_By_GRAMMAR(sentence):
    grammar = ('''
        3WD_ITEMS: 
            {<NN|NNP><,><NN|NNP><CC><NN|NNP>}
        ''')
    #{<DT|CD>?<NN|NNP><,><DT|CD>?<NN|NNP><CC><DT|CD>?<NN|NNP>}
    
    chunker = nltk.RegexpParser(grammar)
    
    token = nltk.word_tokenize(sentence)
   
    tagging = nltk.pos_tag(token)
    #print(tagging)

    if (len(tagging) ==0 ):
        return []
    tree = chunker.parse(tagging)
    #tree.draw()
    #print(tree)
    
    temps = extract_noun_phrases_from_tree(tree,'3WD_ITEMS',False)
    results = []
    for noun_chunk in temps:
        noun_chunk = noun_chunk.replace("or ","and ")
        if (noun_chunk.count(",")==1):
            noun_chunk = noun_chunk.replace("and ",",")
        else:
            noun_chunk = noun_chunk.replace("and ","")
            
        noun_chunk = noun_chunk.replace(" ","")
        parts = noun_chunk.split(",")
        #results.append(parts)
        return parts;
        
  
    return results

from nltk import Tree

grammar = ('''
    NounPhrase: 
        {<DT|CD>?<JJ|JJR|JJS>*<NN|NNS|NNP|NNPS><IN>?<DT|CD>?<JJ|JJR|JJS>*<NN|NNS|NNP|NNPS>*}
    ''')
chunker = nltk.RegexpParser(grammar)

def extract_3WD_phrases(sentence):
    #pre-processing
    sentence = sentence.replace("|"," - ") # special case
    
    
    char_to_replace = {"[": "", "]": ""}
    for key, value in char_to_replace.items():
        sentence = sentence.replace(key, value)

    #splits  = re.split('\s[]\s', sentence)
    sentence = sentence.replace(chr(8211),"-")
    splits  = sentence.split(' - ')
    
    
    
    if len(splits) == 1:
        sentence = splits[0]
    elif len(splits) == 2:
        sentence = splits[0]
    elif len(splits) == 3:
        sentence = splits[0] + " " + splits[2]
    else:
        #print(sentence)
        return []
        #raise Exception("Not handle this case yet")
   
    token = nltk.word_tokenize(sentence)
    #print(token)
    tagging = nltk.pos_tag(token)
    #print(tagging)

    tree = chunker.parse(tagging)
    #tree.draw()
    #DEBUG
    taggings = list(map(lambda sent: Tree(sent[1], children=[sent[0]]), tagging))
    result = chunker.parse(taggings)
    #result.draw()
    
    return extract_noun_phrases_from_tree(tree)

In [756]:
def extract_3WD():

    threeWD_phrases = []
    threeWD_items = []
    nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_md')
    for i, doc in enumerate(data['sentences']):
        phrases = []
        items = []
        for sentence_with_linebreak in doc:

            for sentence in sentence_with_linebreak.split('\n'):  

                if check_three(sentence):
                    extracted_items = extract_3WD_items(sentence)
                    
                    if len(extracted_items) == 0:
                        extracted_items = extract_3WD_ITEMS_By_GRAMMAR(sentence)
                        
                    for phrase in extract_3WD_phrases(sentence):
                        text = remove_words_before_three(phrase)
                        
                        phrases.append(text)
                        if len(extracted_items)>0:
                            items.append({text: extracted_items})
                else:
                    extracted_items = extract_3WD_ITEMS_By_GRAMMAR(sentence)
                    if (len(extracted_items) > 0):
                        
                        items.append({"": extracted_items})
                        
                    
        threeWD_phrases.append(set(phrases))
        threeWD_items.append(items)

    data["3WD_Phrases"] = threeWD_phrases
    data["3WD_Items"] = threeWD_items

# START EXTRACTING DATA
extract_3WD()

def count_document_frequencies(term):
    count = 0;
    for i in range(len(data)):
        document = data['documents'][i]
        if document.find(term)>-1:
            count += 1
    return count

phrase_frequencies = {}

for i in range(len(data)):
    phrases = data['3WD_Phrases'][i]
    for phrase in phrases:
        
        # on document 27, "three" is a noun phrase in the sentence we have all three. This is very special
        # Don't want to count how many documents for this case. Only count for specific such three types, three levels..
        if phrase.strip() == 'three':
            continue
        nr_docs = count_document_frequencies(phrase)

        
        if phrase in phrase_frequencies:
            phrase_frequencies[phrase] += nr_docs
        else:
            phrase_frequencies[phrase] = nr_docs

phrase_frequencies = {k: v for k, v in sorted(phrase_frequencies.items(), key=lambda item: item[1],reverse=True)}

from nltk.corpus import wordnet

def get_wordnet_pos(treebank_tag):

    if treebank_tag.startswith('J'):
        return wordnet.ADJ
    elif treebank_tag.startswith('V'):
        return wordnet.VERB
    elif treebank_tag.startswith('N'):
        return wordnet.NOUN
    elif treebank_tag.startswith('R'):
        return wordnet.ADV
    else:
        return ''

from nltk.stem.wordnet import WordNetLemmatizer
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()

# Lemmatizing each word with its POS tag, in each sentence
data['tokens_sentences_lemmatized'] = data['POS_tokens'].progress_map(
    lambda list_tokens_POS: [
        [
            lemmatizer.lemmatize(el[0], get_wordnet_pos(el[1])) 
            if get_wordnet_pos(el[1]) != '' else el[0] for el in tokens_POS
        ] 
        for tokens_POS in list_tokens_POS
    ]
)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('3topics.png')
plt.show()
